[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16487] updated reedline dep to latest commit (#16487)
@sholderbach:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16486] updated benchmarking README (#16486)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16485] added a benchmark 
``use``
ing the whole 
``std``
 (#16485)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16470] updated PLATFORM_SUPPORT to mention loongarch limitations (#16470)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16469] performed clippy and dead code elimination pass (#16469)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16468] used direct 
``Value.as_str()``
 in string commands (#16468)
@Bahex:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16482] moved 
``SplitRead``
 and 
``MultiLife``
 into 
``nu-utils``
 (#16482)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16428] made 
``watch``
 return a stream of events as a table when called without a closure (#16428)
@app/dependabot:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16480] bumped tempfile from 3.20.0 to 3.21.0 (#16480)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16478] bumped crate-ci/typos from 1.35.4 to 1.35.5 (#16478)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16426] bumped actions/checkout from 4 to 5 (#16426)
@uraneko 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16476] sorted help message flags by required field (#16476)
@132ikl:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16475] added assertion that DeprecationEntry flag do not have dashes (#16475)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16473] mitigated 
``watch -d``
 breaking change (#16473)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16471] made 
``Span``
 mandatory for some fields in 
``ShellError``
 (#16471)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16460] tweaked PR template (#16460)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16458] added "Motivation and technical details" (#16458)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16443] redirected "Questions" issue option to Discussions (#16443)
@weirdan:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16472] made 
``xml:``
 prefix always available in 
``query xml``
 (#16472)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16465] extended nodeset output formats for 
``query xml``
 (#16465)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16461] used fixed column name for 
``query xml``
 output (#16461)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16459] added multiple output types for 
``query xml``
 (#16459)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16440] quoted strings containing 
``=``
 (#16440)
@andoalon:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16466] added 
``--endian``
 flag to 
``into binary``
 (#16466)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16435] changed the output of 
``format bits``
 to big endian instead of native endian (#16435)
@hustcer 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16455] fixed loongarch64 builds for rust 1.87.0 (#16455)
@WindSoilder 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16452] fixed uninlined_format_args clippy warnings (#16452)
@NotTheDr01ds 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16450] added ability to specify a table name for kv commands (#16450)
@cptpiepmatz 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16446] added well-optimized string types (#16446)
@ItsHarper 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/16393] fixed error message: custom commands cannot be 
``const``
 (#16393)
